    {
        "content": "<p><code>simp</code> messes up this Sym2 expression even when explicitly adding <code>Sym2.congr_left</code> to simp lemmas. We should fix that, but I don't know what is the best way to fix it. Anyone cares to look at this?</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">import</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Mathlib</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">variable</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">{</span><span class=\"n\">α</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">Type</span><span class=\"bp\">*</span><span class=\"o\">}</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">{</span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">c</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">α</span><span class=\"o\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">example</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">h</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">s</span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">s</span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">c</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"o\">))</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"gr\">sorry</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">simp</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">Sym2</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">congr_left</span><span class=\"o\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">at</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">h</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">example</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">h</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">s</span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">s</span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">c</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"o\">))</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"gr\">sorry</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">rw</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">Sym2</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">congr_left</span><span class=\"o\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">at</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">h</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 538085005,
        "sender_full_name": "Jakub Nowak",
        "timestamp": 1757257159
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><code>simp [-Sym2.eq, Sym2.congr_left] at h</code></p>",
        "id": 538085465,
        "sender_full_name": "Aaron Liu",
        "timestamp": 1757257630
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Yeah, I know, but I think we should fix it so that simp doesn't messes it up by default.</p>",
        "id": 538085498,
        "sender_full_name": "Jakub Nowak",
        "timestamp": 1757257662
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I'm don't think <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=Sym2.eq#doc\">docs#Sym2.eq</a> is a good <code>@[simp]</code> lemma</p>",
        "id": 538085557,
        "sender_full_name": "Aaron Liu",
        "timestamp": 1757257717
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Or maybe <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=Sym2.rel_iff%27#doc\">docs#Sym2.rel_iff'</a> is a bad <code>@[simp]</code> lemma</p>",
        "id": 538085598,
        "sender_full_name": "Aaron Liu",
        "timestamp": 1757257773
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>definitely we shouldn't have both</p>",
