        "timestamp": 1757332992
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Yes, and if they are really necessary to a domain, maybe create custom simpsets.</p>",
        "id": 538216581,
        "sender_full_name": "Alfredo Moreira-Rosa",
        "timestamp": 1757335727
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I think, that <code>Sym2.eq</code> is pretty bad not only as a simp lemma, but as a lemma too. <code>Sym2.Rel</code> is just an implementation detail of <code>Sym2</code> and there is close to zero API for <code>Sym2.Rel</code>. If there's a theorem that unfolds <code>Sym2 p = Sym2 q</code> it should unfold directly to <code>p = q ∨ p = q.swap</code>, omitting <code>Sym2.Rel</code> altogether.</p>",
        "id": 538222012,
        "sender_full_name": "Jakub Nowak",
        "timestamp": 1757336969
    }
